In this article, President Barack Obama proclaims the week of August 11 through August 17, 2013, as National Health Center Week. The article highlights the importance of community health centers in providing affordable and high-quality healthcare to millions of Americans, regardless of their ability to pay. These health centers play a critical role in helping patients stay healthy and avoid emergency room visits. The article also mentions that health centers employ over 148,000 people nationwide and are important partners in reducing health disparities. The Obama administration has made significant investments in strengthening this essential network through the Affordable Care Act and the Recovery Act. As more Americans gain access to health insurance options through the Affordable Care Act, health centers continue to be valuable in helping community members understand their options and enroll in appropriate plans. The article encourages Americans to celebrate National Health Center Week by visiting their local health center and exploring the programs they offer.